Syntax: poison:arsenic

Applies arsenic poison to your currently wielded weapon. Arsenic is a
slow-acting inorganic poison that deals damage over time when a poisoned
attack lands. It is one of three weapon poisons available to rogue-line
characters (Cipher, Assassin, Warlock, Nightblade).

Each poison type has distinct effects that interact with Backstab and Circle
when applied. Arsenic's damage-over-time profile makes it effective for
sustained pressure in extended fights.

Acquiring poison skills:
  Poison weapon skills are learned through the rogue class progression.
  Use SHELP POISON:ARSENIC for full acquisition details.

Restrictions:
  - Requires a weapon to be wielded.
  - Must have the skill learned.

See also: shelp poison:arsenic poison:quinine poison:nightshade poison weapon backstab
